Process :-
• Add chicken cubes, yogurt, ginger garlic paste, curry leaves, black pepper powder, cumin powder, salt and red chilli powder. 
• Mix and coat the chicken well, set aside to marinate for minimum 30 minutes. 
• After margination, now add rice flour and mix well. 
• Heat oil in a kadhai and deep fry the chicken until crisp. 
• Drain on an absorbent paper and set aside. 
• For tempering heat oil in a pan, add green chillies, garlic and curry leaves, saute till fragrant. 
• Add the fried chicken and toss well. Add black pepper powder and toss well. 
• Serve hot.